* In its [[descriptive ethics|"descriptive"]] sense, ''morality'' refers to [[Value (personal and cultural)|personal or cultural values]], [[code of conduct|codes of conduct]] or social [[mores]]. It does not connote objective claims of right or wrong, but only refers to that which is considered right or wrong. [[Descriptive ethics]] is branch of philosophy which studies definitions of morality.
 
* In its "[[normative]]" sense, ''morality'' is a [[definition]] of right and wrong which excludes [[subjective]] opinion. [[Normative ethics]] is the branch of philosophy concerned with correctly choosing between such definitions.
